   OPTIONS-CONFLICT (Undated) _ The retirement package awarded to
Dick Cheney, the Republican candidate for vice president, is
neither the largest nor the most generous ever given a chief
executive officer. But the $20 million package is remarkable in
other ways. It has brought executive compensation back from the
dead as a campaign issue, and has elevated stock option wealth _
and the potential conflicts it may pose to politicians who have
amassed it _ to center stage. By Gretchen Morgenson.
</P>
