Kan., couple have won $5,000 by naming their just-born baby boy
 &UR; Iuma Dylan-Lucas Thornhill &LR; , his first name in paid homage to
Internet Underground Music Archive of Redwood City.
</P>
<P>
   The company said its offer of the prize, to the first 10 babies
named Iuma born between August 1 and November 1, is ``the final
frontier in online marketing.''
</P>
<P>
   Iuma's father,  &UR; Travis Thornhill &LR; , 22, said he had learned about
the contest the night before the baby was born and discussed it
with his wife,  &UR; Jessica &LR; , 21. They decided to go ahead with the
