<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   QUAKE-ESTIMATE (San Francisco) _ Scientists report that the
northern Hayward Fault in California is less likely to experience a
major quake in the next three decades than previously thought,
reaffirming a similar conclusion issued last year. By KEAY
DAVIDSON.
</P>
<P>
   BUSINESS/FINANCIAL NEWS (``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   SF-AIRPORT (San Francisco) _ The opening of San Francisco
International Airport's new International Terminal may delayed, but
that's not going to delay Nidal Nazzal. Nazzal, who owns Burger
Joint, one of the 16 restaurants slated for the new terminal, plans
to open in mid-September. That's near the terminal's original
opening date of Sept. 26, but well before the Nov. 1 to Dec. 15
time frame that airport officials now believe is more realistic for
the terminal's debut. By VICTORIA COLLIVER.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT (``e'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FILM-HOFFMAN (Undated) _ The sad truth about Abbie Hoffman is
that time has relegated him to little more than an exuberant
footnote to his own revolution. Seventies counterculturalism used
to have several first names among the often-imitated,
never-duplicated Abbie. In ``Steal This Movie`` Hoffman's wit seems
to have been left on the cutting-room floor along with the
stamped-out buds. By WESLEY MORRIS.
