<TEXT>
<P>
   Editors at publications outside the United States may find the
following stories from the New York Times News Service
for &UR; SATURDAY, August 19,  &LR; of particular interest:
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL &LR;
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in `i' news category)
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-SUBMARINE (Moscow) _ Developing: The Russian effort to
save the 118 crew members trapped aboard a sunken submarine was
dealt a serious setback Friday when rescuers reached the deck but
were unable to open the escape hatch, Russian navy officials told
state television. By Patrick E. Tyler.
</P>
