raised some $10 million for his presidential library, plus
California donors kicked in a bundle to bolster Hillary Rodham
Clinton's Senate campaign in New York. That's the way the system
works, and until campaign finance reform becomes a reality (don't
count on it soon), political aspirants will have to have their
hands out. By HELEN THOMAS. (Already filed.)
