<P>
   GORE _ GORELA CROSSE, Wis. _ Al Gore and running mate, Sen.
Joseph Lieberman, wasted little time Friday following the close of
the Democratic National Convention to hurl themselves into the
finals of the campaign for the White House. Gore, summoning the
nation to join him ``on a new journey to the best America,'' dashed
to the crucial battleground states of the industrial Midwest to
begin making his case. Developing. (Shepard, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Expected to move by 6 p.m. EDT on the NYT wire.
