<P>
   RUSSIA-SUNKEN-SUB (Moscow) _ Desperate efforts to save any
survivors from a sunken Russian nuclear submarine meet with a new
setback when a rescue capsule reaches an escape hatch but finds it
too damaged to open. By David Filipov. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   SIMPSONS-MACBETH (Edinburgh, Scotland) _ One of the hits of this
year's Edinburgh Fringe Festival is a one-man play that adapts
Macbeth by casting Homer Simpson as the ambitious, tortured Scot.
By Kevin Cullen. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; POLITICS (p) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CAMPAIGN-GORE (Prairie du Chien, Wis.) _ Al Gore takes his newly
energized campaign to the middle of the country, both
geographically and ideologically, hoping his populist message will
play well in the region that will decide the election. By Michael
Kranish and Susan Milligan. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   CAMPAIGN-BUSH (Memphis, Tenn.) _ George W. Bush returns to the
campaign trail, stopping in his rival's home state, where he
declares ``the battle lines are clearly drawn.'' By Anne E.
Kornblut. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   CONVENTIONS-FASHION (Los Angeles) _ Comparing the look of
delegates, from big hair in Philly to no ties in LA. By Tina
Cassidy and Joanna Weiss. 700 words.
</P>
