   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MOXLEY-TRIAL (Undated) _ The lead prosecutor in the Martha
Moxley murder case says that Connecticut might drop its charges
against Michael Skakel if a trial is ordered in juvenile court. By
Brian MacQuarrie. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   EMERGENCY-LANDING (Undated) _ An AirTran Airways DC-9 made an
emergency landing last week in Greensboro, N.C. when smoke filled
the cockpit and started billowing back into the passenger
compartment. By Matthew Brelis. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   COURTS-EXPERT (Boston) _ In a decision that raises the bar for
expert testimony in court cases, from medical to scientific,
Massachusetts' highest court says judges must hold hearings and
carefully analyze what an expert will say before letting a jury
hear it. By Ralph Ranalli. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; LIFESTYLE (l) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ANIMALS-COLUMN (Undated) _ The latest thinking &UR;  &LR; by a new breed
of bunny activists is that pet rabbits belong indoors. By Vicki
Croke. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   VERIZON-STRIKE (Undated) _ Nearly two weeks after 85,000
telephone workers walked off their jobs at Verizon Communications,
the company created by the merger of Bell Atlantic Corp. and GTE,
cellular telephone and other alternatives offering everything from
directory assistance to nationwide call completion have reduced one
portion of the strike's roar to a whisper. By Diane E. Lewis. 1000
words.
</P>
<P>
   BIG-RED-WIRE (Undated) _ A new company, Big Red Wire.com,
offering free long-distance service, is attracting attention by
running provocative billboards of politicians using the service in
major cities. By Chris Reidy. 900 words.
</P>
