<P>
   HOTEL-BUTLERY-SCHOOL (Undated) _ On butler training school at
the St. Regis Hotel in Manhattan. Alex Witchel writes: ``When I
stayed at the St. Regis a few years ago, I opened the door to a
young woman dressed in white tie and tails who identified herself
as the butler. Since I had no idea what to do with her, I sent her
on her way. A female butler. What a funny idea. During my fifth
hour of butler training last week, I was no longer amused.'' (With
photo)
</P>
<P>
   BLUE-POWER-DRESSING (Undated) _ Based on the women at the
Democratic National Convention, blue is the new power color, the
color that suggests true love and fidelity. By Ruth LaFerla.
</P>
<P>
   MALE-BODIES (Undated) _ The new book, ``The Adonis Complex''
(Free Press), tries to show exhaustively how concerns about body
image have come to dominate, and tyrannize, many American men.
``There's no question that there's a much greater emphasis on male
body image than there was a generation ago,'' said one of the
book's three authors. By Guy Trebay.
</P>
