<P>
   GM-ICAHN (Detroit) _ One of the most famous corporate raiders of
the 1980s and 1990s, Carl Icahn, has begun accumulating a stake in
General Motors, the world's largest company, in a move that will
increase pressure on the automaker to spin off its most valuable
asset, Hughes Electronics. By Keith Bradsher.
</P>
