<HEADLINE>
WORLD NEWS IN BRIEF 
</HEADLINE>
   c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   SRI LANKA: ELECTION CALLED
</P>
<P>
   President Chandrika Kumaratunga dissolved Parliament six days
before the end of its six-year term and called national elections
for Oct. 10. Her constitutional plan for a quasi-federal system
that would give greater autonomy to minority Tamils is dead for
now, but she has said she will revive the proposal _ an effort to
bring peace to a nation embroiled in a civil war with separatist
Tamil militants _ after the elections.
</P>
<P>
   INDIA: BARGAINING OVER ACTOR
</P>
<P>
   Veerappan, the South Indian outlaw who kidnapped a movie star,
had demanded that five Tamil militants be released from jail, and
the state of Tamil Nadu had agreed. But four of the militants
refused to be released on bail, insisting that all charges against
them be dropped before they are freed. Their refusal may further
delay the release of the actor, Rajkumar.  &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
