   (NYT29) NEW YORK -- Aug. 20, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN. AUG. 20 --
EBAY-POWERSELLERS-2 -- Andrew J. Waites from West Front Street in
Hattiesburg, Miss., jumped into e-commerce last year. Waites buys
job lots of clothing in Manhattan and sells the garments on eBay.
His company, Inventory Procurement Services, specializes in selling
shirts, jeans and dresses that retail shops want to get rid of,
usually because they want to make room for new styles and more
seasonable clothing. ``One real advantage of the online auction
sites,'' he says, ``is the ability to reduce expenses, especially
for marketing.'' Waites with a load of goods in Manhattan's Garment
District. (Marilynn K. Yee/The New York Times)
