shops and stay-at-home entrepreneurs -- that offer the bulk of
goods for sale on eBay, underpinning its entire business. Abit
Uygan, owner of Sun jewelry in Los Angeles, looking at ring, formed
a partnership with Nang Nguyen in Hershey, Pa., who bought a ring
from his store on eBay. A partnership has resulted in sales of 800
pieces of jewelry a month and the two men are now considering
taking the company public. (Marissa Roth/The New York Times)
