<HEADLINE>
2ND COSTCO SUSPECT ARRESTED
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RICK ORLOV 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   VAN NUYS, Calif. _ Los Angeles police on Friday announced the
arrest of a Van Nuys man as the second suspect in Sunday's shootout
at a Costco store that left one person dead and three injured.
</P>
<P>
   Ignacio Chavez, 47, was taken into custody without resistance
Wednesday at his home in the 7000 block of Hazeltine Avenue, Police
Chief Bernard Parks said.
</P>
<P>
   Investigators were given a lead on Chavez through a source who
tipped off police about his unregistered vehicle, which had been
seen in the vicinity of the shooting, Parks said. Police kept his
house under surveillance, followed him when he left and arrested
him.
</P>
<P>
   Chavez is believed to be the brother of the other man in
custody, identified as Ramon Gutierrez, 38, of Van Nuys, who was
wounded in his left leg after the shootout and arrested the same
day, said Lt. Jimmy Grayson of the LAPD Robbery-Homicide Division.
</P>
<P>
   Grayson said officers will refer the case to the District
Attorney's Office and seek homicide and robbery charges against the
two. Police, however, would not release pictures of the suspects
because they are still seeking witnesses.
</P>
<P>
   Police also displayed weapons recovered from Gutierrez and from
Chavez's home. These included a Chinese version of an AK-47, an
MAK-90 semiautomatic, a Colt .45 equipped with a silencer, several
ammunition magazines capable of holding 12 to 50 rounds and
hundreds of bullets.
</P>
<P>
   ``This tells me they were professionals and had done this
before,'' Grayson said, adding officers are looking to determine if
the two were responsible for a holdup of a Brinks armored truck
last year.
</P>
<P>
   Gutierrez and Chavez did not live in the same home, Grayson
said. Both men were unemployed and had no families, he said.
</P>
<P>
   The gunfire broke out last Sunday shortly after 2:30 p.m. as
hundreds of shoppers were going in and out of the Costco at 6100
Sepulveda Blvd.
</P>
<P>
   Grayson said the two were stalking an armored car from Sectran
Security Inc.
</P>
<P>
   ``They followed the guard and stood outside the doors with their
weapons hidden in carts,'' Grayson said. ``When the guard came out
of the store, they pulled the weapons and people started scurrying
all over, looking for cover, and bullets started being fired.''
</P>
<P>
   Owen Wolf, 21, of Studio City died in the gunfire. He was a
customer at the store.
</P>
<P>
   The guard was able to get back into the armored car, and the
driver backed into the vehicle the two suspects were using as a
getaway car.
</P>
<P>
   Grayson said that helped lead to the arrest of Gutierrez because
the vehicle broke down with a flat tire.
</P>
<P>
   The detective said Chavez has a prior arrest on suspicion of
robbery, but no record has turned up on Gutierrez.
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
</TEXT>
