<HEADLINE>
BROKEN CHAIR FORCES OUT MEDIATE 
</HEADLINE>
   c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOUISVILLE, Ky. _ The bizarre injury of the week belongs to
Rocco Mediate, the winner of the Buick Open last Sunday. He had to
withdraw Friday after his chair broke while he was sitting outside
the contestant family dining area.
</P>
<P>
   Mediate, who underwent major back surgery in 1994, injured his
right wrist, right shoulder, neck and lower back in the incident.
He played with discomfort and shot a first-round 77, but he decided
he could not continue.
</P>
<P>
   Gaylord Sports, Mediate's management firm, was livid that a
broken chair had led to Mediate's injury.
</P>
<P>
   ``As his management firm, we are beyond disappointment and
particularly upset that Rocco would suffer such consequences due to
something that could have and should have been avoided,'' said the
statement by Gaylord Sports. ``He is missing more than just a
chance at a major championship title. He was in position to
possibly make the President's Cup team by points or as a captain's
selection with a good week of play.''
</P>
<P>
   Several other players withdrew, including Tom Lehman (sore
knee), Jim Carter (undisclosed) and Ben Crenshaw (undisclosed). &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
